her=[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]|date=March 30, 2020|access-date=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Masked Singer series}}\n[[Category:Super Bowl lead-out programs]]\n[[Category:2020 American television seasons]]\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Masked Singer, The}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox reality talent competition\n| name          = The Masked Singer (American TV series){{!}}The Masked Singer\n| logo          = The Masked Singer US S3.jpg\n| caption       =\n| season        = 3\n| num_episodes  = 9<!-- increment when new episode airs -->\n| first_aired   = {{Start date|2020|2|2}}\n| last_aired    = present\n| starring        = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Robin Thicke]]\n*[[Jenny McCarthy]]\n*[[Ken Jeong]]\n*[[Nicole Scherzinger]]\n}}\n| host          = [[Nick Cannon]]\n| broadcaster   = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| last          = The Masked Singer (American season 2)\n| next          = \n| year          = Early 2020\n}}\n\nThe third season of ''[[The Masked Singer (American TV series)|The Masked Singer]]'' premiered on February 2, 2020, as the [[Super Bowl LIV]] [[list of Super Bowl lead-out programs|lead-out program]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://heavy.com/entertainment/2019/12/the-masked-singer-season-3-premiere-date/|title=''The Masked Singer'' Season 3 Premiere Date & Details|date=December 18, 2019|access-date=December 20, 2019|author=D.L. Thompson|website=[[Heavy.com|Heavy]]}}</ref>\n\nDuring the season, eighteen celebrities will compete anonymously in new full-bodied costumes and masks. Before each performance, a video package will tease clues to their identity with the celebrity narrating aspects of their biography in a disguised voice. After each performs in their own voice, the panelists will attempt to guess who is the masked singer. The contestants are then voted on by the audience to see who is safe and continues, or who will compete in a further round of singing in that episode, and possibly elimination.\n\n==Panelists and host==\n{{multiple image\n| total_width   = 420\n| align         = left\n| direction     = horizontal\n| header        = Season 3 panelists and host\n| image1        = Robin Thicke 2019 by Glenn Francis.jpg\n| caption1      = [[Robin Thicke]]\n| image2        = Jenny McCarthy at E3 2006.jpg\n| caption2      = [[Jenny McCarthy]]\n| image3        = Ken Jeong March 2015.jpg\n| caption3      = [[Ken Jeong]]\n| image4        = Nicole Scherzinger 2012.jpg\n| caption4      = [[Nicole Scherzinger]]\n| image5        = Nick Cannon by David Shankbone.jpg\n| caption5      = [[Nick Cannon]] \n}}\n\n[[Nick Cannon]], singer-songwriter [[Robin Thicke]], television personality [[Jenny McCarthy]], actor and comedian [[Ken Jeong]], and recording artist [[Nicole Scherzinger]] will return for their third season as host and panelists.<ref name=\"Season 3 EW\">{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/12/30/what-we-know-the-masked-singer-season-3/|title=What we know (so far) about ''The Masked Singer'' season 3: New costumes, 18 contestants, and more|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|author=Rachel Yang |date=December 30, 2019|access-date=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\nGuest panelists included [[Jamie Foxx]] during the first episode, [[Jason Biggs]] in the second episode, [[Leah Remini]] in the third episode, [[Gabriel Iglesias]] in the fifth episode, season 1 winner, [[T-Pain]], in the sixth episode, [[Joel McHale]] in the eighth episode, [[Will Arnett]] in the ninth episode, [[Sharon Osbourne]] in the eleventh episode,<ref name=\"TFC E11\"/> and [[Yvette Nicole Brown]] in the twelfth episode.<ref>{{cite press release|title=(MS-313) The Mother Of All Final Face Offs, Part 2|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/listings/20200326fox05/|via=[[The Futon Critic]]|publisher=[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]|access-date=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Format==\nDuring the first nine episodes, the 18 singers have been divided up into three groups: Group A, B, and C, with each group having a block of three episodes. During each of the individual Group episodes, all remaining singers from that group perform one song/routine, and the audience then votes for their favorite. The singer with the fewest votes is eliminated from the competition and forced to reveal their identity.\n\n==Contestants==\nDuring the season, eighteen contestants will compete.<ref name=\"Season 3 EW\" /> \n\nThe competitors are said to have a combined 66 [[Grammy Award|Grammy]] nominations, 17 [[RIAA certification|gold records]], 11 [[Super Bowl]] appearances, Three stars on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]],and One title in the [[Guinness World Records|Guinness Book of World Records]].<ref>{{cite web|website=[[TVGuide]]|url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/the-masked-singer-season-3-Jamie Fox/|title=The Masked Singer Season 3 Adds Jamie Fox as Guest Panelist|author= Amanda Bell|date= January 7, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; \"\n|- \n! rowspan=\"3\" | Stage name<ref>{{cite web |title=From the Banana to the Taco, \u2018The Masked Singer\u2019 Season 3 Costumes Have Been Revealed|url=https://variety.com/2020/tv/news/masked-singer-season-3-costumes-first-look-photos-1203485426/|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=January 31, 2020|date=January 29, 2020}}</ref>\n! rowspan=\"3\"| Celebrity\n! rowspan=\"3\"| Occupation\n! colspan=\"10\"| Episodes\n|-\n! colspan=\"1\" |1\n! colspan=\"1\" |2\n! colspan=\"1\" |3\n! colspan=\"1\" |4\n! colspan=\"1\" |5\n! colspan=\"1\" |6\n! colspan=\"1\" |7\n! colspan=\"1\" |8\n! colspan=\"1\" |9\n! rowspan=\"2\" |10\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\"| Group A\n! colspan=\"3\"| Group B\n! colspan=\"3\"| Group C\n|-\n! Kangaroo\n| colspan=2 {{n/a|TBA}}\n| bgcolor=lightgreen | SAFE\n| bgcolor=lightgreen | SAFE\n| bgcolor=lightgreen | SAFE\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#FFEBCD\" |\n| bgcolor=\"#C5AAF5\" | {{efn|name=Group A winners|Kangaroo, Turtle, and White Tiger won 